records.addlTxt:
Defendant Alecya D Wilson in court, in custody, with attorney Jess Martinez.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Repeater enhancer struck upon motion of the State.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

3 Years 1 month Imprisonment (Credit - 63 days )  CONSECUTIVE TO CURRENT SENTENCE
- 1 Year 1 month of Initial Confinement
- 2 Years of Extended Supervision

Term of Probation: 2 Years

Conditions of Probation:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Psychological Evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
- Take a Criminal Thinking Course;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
- No contact with any Boston Store .
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge

COSTS:  $278.00
DNA Surcharge:  $250.00
To be paid as a condition of probation/extended supervision; alternate 53 hours of community service.

Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is not eligible for the Substance Abuse Program

Felony warnings, immigration warnings,  voting rights and firearms warnings given.
